---
import SAGPLayout from "../../../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../../components/PageHero.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="New Event | SAGP Executive Portal">

<PageHero
  kicker="Executive Portal"
  title="Create a New Event"
  subtitle="Turn a finalized Word announcement into a reviewable event draft before anything is published."
  image="/assets/images/parthenon_night.jpg"
/>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div><h2>How it works</h2></div>
  <div>
    <ol>
      <li>Betsy prepares or receives the finalized event announcement as a Microsoft Word document.</li>
      <li>Edward runs the event-draft assistant with the event type and year.</li>
      <li>The assistant extracts the event details and prepares a structured draft.</li>
      <li>The draft is reviewed on the website’s draft preview page and corrected as needed.</li>
      <li>Only an approved draft is promoted to the public event calendar.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="callout">
      Preparing a draft does not publish the event. Review and approval remain
      separate steps.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div><h2>Prepare the announcement</h2></div>
  <div>
    <p>
      The Word document should contain the finalized title, dates, times and
      time zone, location or online-attendance information, sessions, speakers,
      presentation titles, and abstracts when available.
    </p>

    <p>
      Send the document to Edward and identify whether it is an Annual
      Conference or Distinguished Lectureship, along with the event year.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div><h2>Process and review</h2></div>
  <div>
    <p>
      Edward processes the document from the SAGP umbrella repository using
      the AI-assisted event creation command documented in the SysAdmin
      instructions.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a class="button" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/executive/instructions/sysadmin/`}>
        View SysAdmin instructions →
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

</SAGPLayout>
